						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="italic">Hero-stone set up in the temple of Durgā-Paramēśvari.</hi></p>						

						<p>Siṁghaṇa—A.D. 1236.</p>						

						<p>This inscription referring itself to the reign of <hi rend="bold">Siṁghaṇadēva,</hi> is dated in <hi rend="bold">Śaka 1157, Manmatha, Phālguṇa ba. 10, Tuesday,</hi> corresponding to <hi rend="bold">A.D. 1236, March 4, Tuesday.</hi> It records the death of a carpenter named <hi rend="bold">Lakhkhōja</hi> when <hi rend="bold">Pāṇḍyadēva</hi> of <hi rend="bold">Haluvāgilu</hi> attacked <hi rend="bold">Ajjaḍi.</hi> </p>						

						</summary>
